# API Routes

The application uses Next.js App Router API routes in `/src/app/api/` for server-side operations.

## Products API

- [src/app/api/products/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/products/route.ts)
  - `GET`: Search and filter products with pagination
  - `POST`: Create new products with validation

- [src/app/api/products/[id]/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/products/[id]/route.ts)
  - `GET`: Fetch a specific product by ID
  - `PATCH`: Update product details
  - `DELETE`: Deactivate or delete a product

## Categories API

- [src/app/api/categories/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/categories/route.ts): CRUD operations for categories
- [src/app/api/categories/search/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/categories/search/route.ts): Search categories

## Inventory API

- [src/app/api/inventory/[id]/add-stock/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/inventory/[id]/add-stock/route.ts): Add stock to inventory
- [src/app/api/inventory/[id]/remove-stock/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/inventory/[id]/remove-stock/route.ts): Remove stock
- [src/app/api/inventory/[id]/adjust-stock/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/inventory/[id]/adjust-stock/route.ts): Adjust stock levels

## Sales API

- [src/app/api/sales/report/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/sales/report/route.ts): Generate sales reports
- [src/app/api/sales/[id]/refund/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/sales/[id]/refund/route.ts): Process refunds
